      "parameters": {
        "content": "## SIGNAL 1 — Open 60+ Days [W:7]\nLooks at the postedAt date on the job post. Calculates how many days ago it was posted. If it's 60 days or more → company has been trying to fill this role for 2+ months and failing → score +7.\n\n## SIGNAL 2 — Role Reposted [W:8]\nChecks the isReposted field PhantomBuster gives us directly. If true → company posted this same role before, it didn't get filled, they're posting it again → score +8.\n\n## SIGNAL 3 — Generalist Agency [W:6]\nScans the companyName for agency keywords like \"consulting\", \"staffing\", \"recruitment\", \"partners\", \"solutions\". If the company posting a senior role is actually a generic agency → they have no specialized search capability for this level → score +6.\n\n## SIGNAL 4 — Senior Role Open [W:7]\nChecks if any of the company's job titles contain keywords like \"CTO\", \"VP Engineering\", \"Head of Engineering\", \"Principal Engineer\", \"Technical Lead\". If yes → they have a leadership gap open → score +7.\n\n## SIGNAL 5 — Seniority Mismatch [W:6]\nChecks if the salary field exists AND looks low for a senior title. Senior title + low/junior salary range = they don't understand what this hire costs → score +6. Currently limited because most DACH posts don't list salary.\n\n## SIGNAL 6 — Recent Funding + Leadership Gap [W:9]\nCombines two Apollo data points: recentFunding (funded within last 24 months) AND hasSeniorRole (Signal 4 was true). Company just got money AND has a senior role they can't fill → classic HEAD|MATCH situation → score +9.\n\n## SIGNAL 7 — Placeholder in Senior Role [W:8]\nUses Apollo's employeeCount. If company is 100–200 employees AND has a senior role open → at that size they likely have someone acting as placeholder in the role (junior covering for missing senior) → score +8.\n\n\nNEW\nSignal 5 — HR team ≤ 3% + 100+ employees + senior role open → +6\nSignal 6 — Company growing 15%+ YoY + senior role open → +9 (replaces funding logic)\nSignal 7 — HR team ≤ 5% + 100+ employees + senior role open → +8 (replaces placeholder inference)\nSignal 10 — Average tenure < 2.5 years → +7 (new node, connected to Merge input 9)",
